The paper deals with Interactive Information Retrieval (IIR) experiments and proposes a software tool for analyzing eye tracking data on web pages. This involves analyzing the HTML structure of the web pages to identify what has been viewed and read by the subjects. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category, as it deals with user behavior and interaction with technology. It also involves Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with analyzing textual content on web pages. Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Multimedia (cs.MM) could also be relevant as the paper deals with analyzing gaze behavior on visual stimuli.
